Patricia Plunkett https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patricia_Plunkett 0 Patricia Ruth Plunkett (17 December 1926 – 13 October 1974) was an English actress. Born in Streatham, London, she trained at RADA and had an early stage hit in Pick-Up Girl (1946) by the American dramatist Elsa Shelley.Plunkett appeared in 12 films. She was usually in supporting roles, but she was the female lead (with above-the-title billing) in both her 1949 films: Landfall and For Them That Trespass. The best known of her supporting roles is probably It Always Rains on Sunday (1947), in which her character, Doris Sandigate, is the step-daughter of Rose (Googie Withers), the leading role.
